title: For Sale:  Warning about bulk ammo in Fernely
postcontent:
I bought a thousand rounds for $250. When I started shooting the bullets they would smoke then stick in my gun. If I had been doing double taps the weapon would have exploded in my hands.  I take that seriously. The person in Fernely that sold me this junk acts like he is a smart ass salesman and some kind of smooth operator.  So I'm letting people on ARMSLIST know what kind of experience I had buying bulk ammo.  
Hopefully someone who is thinking of buying bulk ammo from a dude in fernely  will think twice about it and not end up permanently handicapped or dead due to faulty sub-standard ammunition.  Be warned.
